Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Halve and peel the @red onion{1}, then cut each half into 3 wedges. Cut the @medium tomato{2} into 2cm chunks.

Pop both veg onto a #baking tray{}. Drizzle with oil, season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Roast on the middle shelf of your oven until softened, ~{12-15%minutes}.

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{3}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Tear the @ciabatta{1} into roughly 2cm chunks and add to another baking tray. Add half the garlic, drizzle with @olive oil{3%tbsp} and toss to coat well.

Bake the garlic croutons on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{8-10%minutes}, then remove from the oven and set aside.

While everything cooks, drain the @sweetcorn{150%g} in a #sieve{}. Heat a large #frying pan{} on high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the sweetcorn and cook until charred, ~{5-6%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary. Stir only twice during this time - you want the sweetcorn to pick up some nice colour.

While the sweetcorn cooks, zest and halve the @lime{1}. Halve the @avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out onto a board, face-down. Cut into 1cm thick chunks.

Next, drain the @mixed beans{1%carton} in a sieve. Reduce the heat of the pan to medium-high and add a drizzle of oil.

Add the remaining garlic to the sweetcorn and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the mixed beans and @chipotle paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} and cook for ~{1-2%minutes} more.

While the bean mixture cooks, in a large #bowl{}, squeeze in the lime juice and add the lime zest.

Stir in the @honey{1%tbsp} and @olive oil{3%tbsp} for the dressing. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{} then mix together.

When the veg is ready, add the roast veg, bean mixture, avocado and @wild rocket{20%g} to the bowl. Taste and season if needed, then mix to combine.

Add the garlic croutons to the salad, then toss to coat in the dressing.

Divide the Mexican style salad between your bowls.

Crumble over the @Greek style salad cheese{50%g} to finish.

Enjoy!

> Our Mexican Style Roasted Veg Salad is a delicious veggie option that makes it easy to eat more veg in your diet and try something new!
> The chipotle paste adds a smoky heat - adjust to taste if you prefer milder.